    "summary": "Samsara Maintenance & Fault Monitoring combines fault-code and tell-tale reads with DVIR, defect, odometer, and engine-runtime APIs, and it also supports maintenance write workflows such as creating mechanic DVIRs and resolving DVIRs or defects.",
    "description": "Manufactured OpenAPI artifact for Maintenance & Fault Monitoring. This file was synthesized by Last Mile from curated research JSON and is not vendor-certified. Use it as an agent-consumable starting point, then validate paths, schemas, authentication, and server URLs with the vendor before production use. The Maintenance & Fault Monitoring umbrella links four operational areas: fault-code monitoring, tell-tale monitoring, DVIR/defect management, and planned/preventative maintenance. Faults and tell tales are exposed through the vehicle stats snapshot, history, and feed endpoints, while DVIRs and defects have dedicated listing and patch flows. The DVIR guide also documents `POST /fleet/dvirs`, `PATCH /fleet/dvirs/:id`, and `PATCH /fleet/defects/:id`, which confirms real writeback capability in addition to read-heavy maintenance telemetry.",
